<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.572/30: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-31T21:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            31, 1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 31, 9 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>520. Your 397 and 490.<note n="58" xml:id="d57fn58">No. 490 of Jan.
                                    30, 2 p.m., not printed.</note> Consider it desirable that
                                Treaty of Commerce and Navigation [with] Norway, with exception of
                                articles 13 and 14, be continued for time being and that similar
                                course be adopted in connection with Spanish treaty. Lansing.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>